MOSCOW, Oct. 25 (Xinhua) -- At least four people were injured as a result of an explosion in a five-story apartment building in the Russian city of Naberezhnye Chelny, local media reported Monday. Six apartments on the last two floors of the building were destroyed following the explosion, TASS news agency reported, citing a source from the emergency services. According to preliminary information, four people were injured following the blast and 32 were evacuated from the site. Several people could be under the debris. A gas leak could be behind the explosion, said the report citing the source. Enditem